 Mthatha - Three female students are expected in court soon after they were arrested by police following a student protest at Ikhala FET College at Ezibeleni on Tuesday night, at about 23:00 "It is alleged that the students were protesting neat the gate of the College burning tryes and throwing stones at the college," said police spokesperson, Brigadier Tembinkosi Kinana. "Police attended the scene and arrested the students and a case of Public Violence case was opened and all suspects will appear   before the Ezibeleni Magistrate's Court soon." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 